29. Use Flutter to Implement Gesture in App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

In Flutter, gestures are used to detect user interactions like:

Tap
Double tap
Long press
Swipe

The GestureDetector widget is used to handle these interactions.


// main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: GestureExample(),
    );
  }
}

class GestureExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Gesture Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: GestureDetector(
          onTap: () {
            print("Container Tapped");
          },
          onDoubleTap: () {
            print("Double Tapped");
          },
          onLongPress: () {
            print("Long Pressed");
          },
          child: Container(
            height: 150,
            width: 250,
            color: Colors.orange,
            child: Center(
              child: Text(
                "Tap Me",
                style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 20),
              ),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}